ph-transit-graph-api

> Community-driven route and fare data API for Philippine transit.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
STACK
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Spring Boot 3.5
Spring Data JPA + Hibernate
PostgreSQL 16
Maven
Lombok
Bean Validation

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
GETTING STARTED
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Prerequisites
- Java 21+
- PostgreSQL
- Maven

Setup
  git clone https://github.com/kuwarte/ph-transit-graph-api.git
  cd ph-transit-graph-api
  cp .env.example .env
  mvn spring-boot:run

Database
  CREATE DATABASE ph_transit_graph;
  CREATE USER transituser WITH PASSWORD 'yourpassword';
  GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE ph_transit_graph TO transituser;
  GRANT ALL ON SCHEMA public TO transituser;

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
API ENDPOINTS
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Base URL: http://localhost:8080/api/v1

Places
  GET    /places
  GET    /places/{id}
  GET    /places/search?municipality=&province=
  POST   /places
  PUT    /places/{id}
  DELETE /places/{id}

Routes
  GET    /routes
  GET    /routes/{id}
  GET    /routes/search?origin=&destination=
  GET    /routes/vehicle/{type}
  GET    /routes/code/{routeCode}
  POST   /routes
  PUT    /routes/{id}
  PATCH  /routes/{id}/status
  DELETE /routes/{id}

Stops
  GET    /routes/{routeId}/stops
  GET    /routes/{routeId}/stops/{stopId}
  POST   /routes/{routeId}/stops
  PUT    /routes/{routeId}/stops/{stopId}
  PATCH  /routes/{routeId}/stops/reorder
  DELETE /routes/{routeId}/stops/{stopId}

